HTML - hyper text markup language

- web Page - to create
- Not a programming language
- its a markup language
- Every website starts with HTML

1. Heading - p
   h1 to h6

2. Paragraph - p

3. hr

4. br

5. text formating
   b or strong, mark, i, sub, sup and u

6. Anchor tag - a

7. image tag - img

8. list - two
   order list and unorder list

9. tables - table < tr < th and td

10. forms
    input and label

11. media tags - video and audio

12. sematic Tags
    header, footer, nav, section, aside

CSS - cascading style sheet

1. types of css
   i - inline
   ii - internal
   iii - enternal

inline > internal > external

2. CSS Synatx
   selector{
   property:value;
   }

3. Types of Selectors
   i - Element selector h1, p
   ii - Class selector (.) multiple
   iii - id selector (#) unique
   iv - universal selector (\*)
   v - group selector (h1,h2,p)

4. colors and Background
   background-color : lightblue;
   background-image : url(");
   background-repeat: no-repeat;
   background-size: cover;
   background-position: center;

5. text Styling
   font- family : times new roman;
   font-size: 20px;
   text-align: center;
   text-transform: uppercase;
   text-decoration: line-through;
   font-weight: bolder;
   line-height: 1.7;
   letter-spacing: 100px;

6. Box modeling
   margin, padding, border and content

7. flex

flex direction - row, row-reverse, column, column-reverse

justtfy content (X) - start, center, end, space-between, space-evenly, space-around

align-items (y) - start, center, end

flex-wrap - no wrap, wrap, wrap-reverse

Align-content (y) (flex-wrap only enable then only align content will act) - start, center, end, Space-around, space-between, space-evenly

flex(on items) - flex:1 (grow)

gap - values

order - change the visual order of flex property....

8. Positioning
   i - static - default
   ii - Relative - move to some places
   iii - Absolute - along with non - static parents
   iv - fixed - fixed to the web page
   v - sticky -

9. grid - 2 dimensional layout system.

